SIMPLE: seclusion
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seclusion
<hw>Se*clu"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Seclude</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of secluding, or the state of
being secluded; separation from society or connection; a withdrawing;
privacy; <as>as, to live in <ex>seclusion</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O blest <qex>seclusion</qex> from a jarring world, which he, thus
occupied, enjoys!</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Solitude; separation; withdrawment; retirement;
privacy. See <er>Solitude</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seclusive</ent>⟦br⟧
